`.lathe/agents/verifier.md` written. Here's what it encodes:

**Project shape detected: infrastructure-as-code / service platform.** No registry publish, no preview URL, no dev server — the product is a Kubernetes cluster. Verification is a three-tier ladder: static gates always, full-corpus when iterating charts, kind runtime when the change is only breakable at runtime.

**Key verifier focuses for this project:**

- **_globals/ edge case** — every chart-iterating script that uses bare `grep` under `set -euo pipefail` will silently exit on `_globals/`. The verifier specifically checks this.
- **Four-part chart checklist** — new charts need chart dir + ArgoCD app manifest + namespace in network-policies + `helm dependency update`. The builder misses one of these reliably.
- **Ambition alignment** — four named destinations (VPS bootstrap walkable, Backstage SSO, code-server autarky, uniform HA gate). When a patch defers one of these, the verifier names it in the whiteboard and commits an adversarial test.
- **Test suite conventions** — `scripts/ralph/tests/` runs with plain `python3`, not pytest. Tests must emit `PASS:` lines and end with `All tests passed.` — the verifier checks this before accepting new tests.
- **Witnessing requirement** — CI passing is not enough. The verifier reports what it ran and what it saw, and documents any blocker (no kind cluster available) explicitly.
